The '''Argentine Formula Renault Championship''', formerly known as '''Formula Renault 2.0 Argentina''' and '''Formula Renault 1.6 Argentina''', is an [[open wheel racing]] series founded in 1980. It is based in [[Argentina]].
==Regulations== Since 2010 the cars have been powered by a 2000cc [[Renault]] production engine. Prior to this (from the series' inception in 1980 to 2009) the cars were powered by a 1600cc [[Renault]] production engine. Tito is currently the only [[chassis]] make allowed. Similar Tito 02 cars are used in the [[Chilean Formula Three Championship]].
Tyres are allocated to each driver in sets of 4 at each race meeting.
